updatedAt` | `Instant` | `updated_at` | NO | |\n| `interrupted` | `boolean` | `interrupted` | NO | Default false |\n| `attributeFingerprint` | `String` | `attribute_fingerprint` | NO | Max length 255 |\n| `lastReqVersion` | `String` | `last_req_version` | NO | Max length 50 |\n| `reprocessState` | `ReprocessState` (Enum) | `reprocess_state` | NO | Default: NONE; values: NONE, INIT, RUNNING, SUCCESS, FAILED |\n\n**Annotations**: `@Data`, `@Builder`, `@NoArgsConstructor`, `@AllArgsConstructor`, `@Entity`, `@Table(name = \"entities\")`\n\n---\n\n### EntityService Interface\n\n**Package**: `com.fortinet.nac.ingestion.service`\n\n**Method Signatures**:\n\n```java\nEntity getById(Long id);\n\nvoid save(Entity entity);\n\nvoid saveBatch(Collection<Entity> entityList);\n\nboolean isInterrupted(long entityId);\n\nboolean setInterrupted(Long entityId, boolean interrupted);\n\nEntity getEntity(Long id);\n\nEntity getEntity(IngestionRequest req);\n\nPagination<Entity> queryFailedEntities(EntityQueryDTO req);\n\nboolean isProcessingFinished(Long entityId);\n\nboolean updateProcessingState(Entity fresh);\n\nList<Entity> findStuckEntities(Duration staleThreshold, int maxCount);\n\nMarkForReprocessResult markAllForReprocess();\n\nList<Long> findTopNIdsByReprocessState(ReprocessState state, int limit);\n\nEntityProcessLockInfo findProcessLockInfoById(Long id);\n\nboolean claimInitEntityForReprocess(Long id);\n\nboolean updateReprocessStateById(Long id, ReprocessState state);\n```\n\n---\n\n### EntityServiceImpl Implementation\n\n**Package**: `com.fortinet.nac.ingestion.service`\n\n**Class Name**: `EntityServiceImpl`\n\n**Dependencies Injected**:\n- `EntityRepository entityRepository`\n- `IdService idService` (qualifier: \"IngestionIdService\")\n- `PlatformTransactionManager transactionManager`\n- `MeterRegistry meterRegistry`\n\n**Key Implementation Details**:\n\n1. **`save(Entity entity)`**: \n   - Generates ID using idService if null\n   - Sets createdAt and updatedAt timestamps to current Instant\n   - Delegates to `entityRepository.save()`\n\n2. **`saveBatch(Collection<Entity> entityList)`**:\n   - Batch processes entities with ID generation and timestamp setting\n   - Calls `entityRepository.saveAll()`\n\n3. **`queryFailedEntities(EntityQueryDTO req)`**:\n   - Uses JPA Specification for dynamic query building\n   - Filters by processingStage (optional)\n   - Filters by processingCode (!= 0 unless specific code provided)\n   - Supports sorting by processingStage, type, or createdAt (default)\n   - Supports asc/desc order (default: desc)\n   - Returns paginated Pagination<Entity> with page metadata\n\n4. **`updateProcessingState(Entity fresh)`**:\n   - Marked with `@Transactional(propagation = Propagation.REQUIRES_NEW)`\n   - Updates: interrupted, attributeFingerprint, processingStage, processingCode, lastReqVersion, processingResult, updatedAt\n   - Returns boolean (rows > 0)\n\n5. **`markAllForReprocess()`**:\n   - Batch processes entities needing reprocessing in configurable batch sizes (default 1000)\n   - Each batch runs in a separate transaction (PROPAGATION_REQUIRES_NEW)\n   - Returns `MarkForReprocessResult` with: updatedCount, failedBatches, failedCount\n   - Metrics tracking: `policy_reprocess_mark_init_run_seconds` (tagged by result: success/partial_failure/failed)\n\n6. **`claimInitEntityForReprocess(Long id)`**:\n   - Marked with `@Transactional(propagation = Propagation.REQUIRES_NEW)`\n   - Atomic operation: moves entity from INIT → RUNNING only if current state is INIT\n   - Prevents race conditions with exclusive state transition\n\n---\n\n### EntityRepository Interface\n\n**Package**: `com.fortinet.nac.ingestion.repository`\n\n**Extends**: `JpaRepository<Entity, Long>, JpaSpecificationExecutor<Entity>`\n\n**Query Methods**:\n\n```java\nOptional<Entity> findFirstByTypeAndHostIdentity(EntityType type, String hostIdentity);\n\nOptional<Entity> findFirstByTypeAndHostIdentityAndUserIdentity(EntityType type, String hostIdentity, String userIdentity);\n\n@Modifying\n@Query(\"update Entity e set e.interrupted = :interrupted, e.updatedAt = :updatedAt where e.id = :id\")\nint updateInterrupted(Long id, boolean interrupted, Instant updatedAt);\n\n@Modifying\n@Query(\"update Entity e set e.interrupted = :interrupted, e.attributeFingerprint = :fp, e.processingStage = :stage, e.processingCode = :code, e.lastReqVersion = :version, e.processingResult = :processingResult, e.updatedAt = :updatedAt where e.id = :id\")\nint updateProcessingState(Long id, boolean interrupted, String fp, String stage, Integer code, String version, String processingResult, Instant updatedAt);\n\n@Query(\"select e from Entity e where e.processingStage <> 'ENFORCED' and (e.processingCode = 0 or e.processingCode is null) and e.updatedAt < :before order by e.updatedAt asc\")\nPage<Entity> findStuckEntities(Instant before, Pageable pageable);\n\n@Query(\"SELECT e.id FROM Entity e WHERE e.id > :lastId AND (e.reprocessState <> :targetState OR e.reprocessState IS NULL) ORDER BY e.id\")\nList<Long> findTopNIdsNeedMarkForReprocess(Long lastId, ReprocessState targetState, Pageable pageable);\n\n@Modifying\n@Query(\"UPDATE Entity e SET e.reprocessState = :targetState, e.updatedAt = CURRENT_TIMESTAMP WHERE e.id IN :ids AND (e.reprocessState <> :targetState OR e.reprocessState IS NULL)\")\nint markBatchForReprocess(List<Long> ids, ReprocessState targetState);\n\n@Query(\"SELECT e.id FROM Entity e WHERE e.reprocessState = :state ORDER BY e.id\")\nList<Long> findTopNIdsByReprocessState(ReprocessState state, Pageable pageable);\n\n@Query(\"SELECT e.id AS id, e.type AS type, e.hostId AS hostId, e.adapterId AS adapterId, e.userId AS userId, e.reprocessState AS reprocessState FROM Entity e WHERE e.id = :id\")\nOptional<EntityProcessLockInfo> findProcessLockInfoById(Long id);\n\n@Modifying\n@Query(\"UPDATE Entity e SET e.reprocessState = 'RUNNING', e.updatedAt = :updatedAt WHERE e.id = :id AND e.reprocessState = 'INIT'\")\nint claimInitEntityFo